title: For Sale:  For Sale: Several Guns- New AR15 w/gunsight, FN FS2000 5.56 bullpup, Glock 26 w/night sights, some ammo
location: New Mexico, New Mexico, United States
postcontent:
Hi. Got several items for sale, so bear with me.

First up is my new AR15. It's been test fired a few times in order to check that it can cycle steel cased ammunition and brass cased ammunition. It has a 16" barrel with a carbine length gas system.  

Specs:
Palmetto State Armory 16" upper, barrel is chrome moly vanadium chrome lined. M4 chamber/feedramps, magnesium phosphated to the standard black color. A2 flash hider, fixed front sight block with tritium front sight post (glows in the dark!). Magpul MOE flat dark earth carbine length handguards. T-marked upper receiver. Bolt and carrier are Colt manufacture, charging handle is standard charging handle but unknown manufacture. Rear sight is a Troy Battlesight flip-up BUIS diopter with tritium in flat dark earth to match furniture.

Lower is built on a GAR Arms (Local to Las Cruces, NM) forged aluminum lower receiver. Lower parts kit is a Palmetto State Armory parts kit with Magpul MOE stock, MOE+ grip (I believe) and trigger guard in flat dark earth with standard selector and trigger. 

On top of the rifle sits an Elcan SpecterDR 1-4x gunsight. This is a top of the line gunsight, and it really shows. It doesn't have traditional magnification; instead, changing your magnification from 1x to 4x is done by flipping a throw lever. It has small iron sights sitting on top. The reticle is etched into the glass and has a ballistic drop compensator built in. Illumination goes two ways, adjust one way and it illuminates a 1.5MOA dot, adjust the other way and the entire reticle is illuminated. Very night gunsight, has been mounted but not zeroed yet.

I am asking $4300 for the rifle, that will include a couple 30rd magazines, an aftermarket trigger (Geissele SD3G trigger, used for competition shooting), original grips and front post, and a SIRT training bolt (replaces regular bolt and charging handle and allows the operator to practice trigger discipline, snap shooting, etc. by emitting a green laser every time trigger is pulled). This rifle is truly badass.

Next is an FN FS2000, bought in 2010 and has 500 rounds through it. It has both the smooth foregrip and the railed FN foregrip. This bullpup rifle is pretty badass and fits a full length barrel into a relatively compact space. Flattop with Magpul MBUS flip up sights.

 Asking $2500 for the rifle+ things that came with the rifle, for an extra $250 I can throw in an Eotech holographic sight that was zeroed with this rifle. 

Next up is a Gen 3 Glock 26 with brand-new Meprolight night sights. These are bright as HELL, and you can literally see the gun across the room at night. It has roughly 75 rounds down the pipe and comes with two 10rd magazines, box, lock, etc. Comes with a 3.5lb Ghost Rocket trigger bar and Glock factory extended slide release installed. 

Asking $625 for the Glock. 

Lastly, I can part with some ammo if I am made a good enough offer. I have:

130rds Winchester military-issue (green hull, blacked out rim) 12GA 00 buckshot. This stuff shoots about 9 00 pellets at a ridiculous ~1325 FPS (or something like that.) I am asking $175 for this lot of ammunition (it's all in 5rd nondescript cardboard boxes from the factory.)

400rds Winchester White Box 115gr 9mm FMJ. (brass cased/reloadable.) Asking $175 for this lot.

100rds Winchester White Box 230gr. 45ACP FMJ (brass cased, reloadable). Asking $60 for this lot.

50 rds PMC Bronze 230gr. brass cased .45ACP. Asking $30 for this.

4 boxes Speer Lawman TMJ .40SW TMJ. This is about 250 rounds,  brass cased and reloadable. Asking $100 for this lot.

Finally, if you want to take EVERYTHING in this lot, I will accept $7500 cash for the entire thing. This will include delivery to anywhere in the state of New Mexico. By making an offer you are relinquishing me of any and all liability for anything once the ammunition and/or firearm changes hands from me to you. By making an offer you also state that you are a New Mexico resident, United States citizen, and that there is nothing that would prevent you from legally possessing these items (domestic abuse conviction, drug charges, mental illness, felony convictions). If you want, I will write a bill of sale and would prefer to see New Mexico ID of some sort- Identification card, driver's license, or New Mexico Concealed Handgun License at the time of our transaction.

Thanks for looking, more pictures will be available upon request. If you don't like my prices, then make an offer- all I can say is no.

I am not taking trades, but I will say that the only thing I'm currently interested in is a Benelli semi-auto shotgun. 

I will be at the gun show in Alamogordo on Saturday, April 6 at 9am. I will be wearing a  plain gray shirt with "ASK ME ABOUT MY STUFF FOR SALE!" written on it. It would be easiest to make a deal there, but I can be reached through this ad as well.

title: For Sale:  For Sale: Brand New NICE AR15, FN FS2000 5.56 bullpup, Glock 26 w/night sights, some ammunition
location: New Mexico, New Mexico, United States
postcontent:
Hi. Got several items for sale, so bear with me.

First up is my new AR15. It's been test fired a few times in order to check that it can cycle steel cased ammunition and brass cased ammunition. It has a 16" barrel with a carbine length gas system.  

Specs:
Palmetto State Armory 16" upper, barrel is chrome moly vanadium chrome lined. M4 chamber/feedramps, magnesium phosphated to the standard black color. A2 flash hider, fixed front sight block with tritium front sight post (glows in the dark!). Magpul MOE flat dark earth carbine length handguards. T-marked upper receiver. Bolt and carrier are Colt manufacture, charging handle is standard charging handle but unknown manufacture. Rear sight is a Troy Battlesight flip-up BUIS diopter with tritium in flat dark earth to match furniture.

Lower is built on a GAR Arms (Local to Las Cruces, NM) forged aluminum lower receiver. Lower parts kit is a Palmetto State Armory parts kit with Magpul MOE stock, MOE+ grip (I believe) and trigger guard in flat dark earth with standard selector and trigger. 

On top of the rifle sits an Elcan SpecterDR 1-4x gunsight. This is a top of the line gunsight, and it really shows. It doesn't have traditional magnification; instead, changing your magnification from 1x to 4x is done by flipping a throw lever. It has small iron sights sitting on top. The reticle is etched into the glass and has a ballistic drop compensator built in. Illumination goes two ways, adjust one way and it illuminates a 1.5MOA dot, adjust the other way and the entire reticle is illuminated. Very night gunsight, has been mounted but not zeroed yet.

I am asking $4300 for the rifle, that will include a couple 30rd magazines, an aftermarket trigger (Geissele SD3G trigger, used for competition shooting), original grips and front post, and a SIRT training bolt (replaces regular bolt and charging handle and allows the operator to practice trigger discipline, snap shooting, etc. by emitting a green laser every time trigger is pulled). This rifle is truly badass.

Next is an FN FS2000, bought in 2010 and has 500 rounds through it. It has both the smooth foregrip and the railed FN foregrip. This bullpup rifle is pretty badass and fits a full length barrel into a relatively compact space. Flattop with Magpul MBUS flip up sights.

 Asking $2500 for the rifle+ things that came with the rifle, for an extra $250 I can throw in an Eotech holographic sight that was zeroed with this rifle. 

Next up is a Gen 3 Glock 26 with brand-new Meprolight night sights. These are bright as HELL, and you can literally see the gun across the room at night. It has roughly 75 rounds down the pipe and comes with two 10rd magazines, box, lock, etc. Comes with a 3.5lb Ghost Rocket trigger bar and Glock factory extended slide release installed. 

Asking $625 for the Glock. 

Lastly, I can part with some ammo if I am made a good enough offer. I have:

130rds Winchester military-issue (green hull, blacked out rim) 12GA 00 buckshot. This stuff shoots about 9 00 pellets at a ridiculous ~1325 FPS (or something like that.) I am asking $175 for this lot of ammunition (it's all in 5rd nondescript cardboard boxes from the factory.)

400rds Winchester White Box 115gr 9mm FMJ. (brass cased/reloadable.) Asking $175 for this lot.

100rds Winchester White Box 230gr. 45ACP FMJ (brass cased, reloadable). Asking $60 for this lot.

50 rds PMC Bronze 230gr. brass cased .45ACP. Asking $30 for this.

4 boxes Speer Lawman TMJ .40SW TMJ. This is about 250 rounds,  brass cased and reloadable. Asking $100 for this lot.

Finally, if you want to take EVERYTHING in this lot, I will accept $7500 cash for the entire thing. This will include delivery to anywhere in the state of New Mexico. By making an offer you are relinquishing me of any and all liability for anything once the ammunition and/or firearm changes hands from me to you. By making an offer you also state that you are a New Mexico resident, United States citizen, and that there is nothing that would prevent you from legally possessing these items (domestic abuse conviction, drug charges, mental illness, felony convictions). If you want, I will write a bill of sale and would prefer to see New Mexico ID of some sort- Identification card, driver's license, or New Mexico Concealed Handgun License at the time of our transaction.

Thanks for looking, more pictures will be available upon request. If you don't like my prices, then make an offer- all I can say is no.

I am not taking trades at this time, but I really want a Benelli semi-auto shotgun.

I will be at the gun show in Alamogordo on Saturday, April 6 at 9am. I will be wearing a  plain gray shirt with "ASK ME ABOUT MY STUFF FOR SALE!" written on it. It would be easiest to make a deal there, but I can be reached through this ad as well.

postcontent:
Solvent can trap connectors made here in Kansas City Missouri
These connectors are used to attach common oil filters to your muzzle to trap solvents for reuse and saving the environment.

304 Stainless steel that's corrosion resistant and many times stronger than aluminum

1/2-28 internal thread fits threaded barrels from .22Lr up to some .30 caliber

This will fit
Ar-15
Gsg
Ruger 10-22
Mossberg 715
Remington 597
9mm threaded barrels
.22Lr threaded barrels
And many many more

3/4-16 outer threads is the single most popular oil filter thread

The filter on the connector holds a little more than 1/3 qt of solvent
The largest for this thread holds more than a quart

I recommend punching a hole in the end of the filter and plugging with a rubber plug (not included) to allow easier draining without removal while cleaning.
Do NOT drill the hole. That will contaminate your filter. I would use a metal rod from the inside of the filter and punch it through to the outside. Usually slightly larger than the bore of the firearm to allow proper draining.

postcontent: This was built from the receiver up to be more or less a DMR gun. Receiver came off a standard M1A. I do not recall who the rifle was built by, I bought it second hand. title: For Sale:  1942 Lithgow Lee-Enfield No 1 mk. III*
postcontent:
This No. 1 mk III* is a WW2 Australia gun, manufactured in 1942. Imported during the early 1960's (older import mark  on barrel knox), it was sporterized for hunting not long after. 

Overall, this gun is in excellent shape: the original stock was cut down very neatly, and the old swivel butt mounts were well filled in. The original fore and back sights are still present, and the barrel has not been counterbored or cut down. The bore is very, very clean. 

This gun has a numbers-matching action and barrel, and the mag/bolt/backsight all have identical (but different from the action) numbers. This is typical for factory-refurbished weapons coming back from repair. Of course, it's chambered in .303 British

This Enfield would make a spectacular project gun, but shoots great and is enjoyable just the way it is. I'm selling to buy another Enfield, actually.  Emails or text to three30-72seven-267five. Thanks!

I'd prefer cash, but am open to trades. Make me a reasonable offer. Face to face transactions preferred, I'll ship to an FFL provided the buyer agrees to shipping charges.

title: For Sale:  TEC 12 12GA PUMP/SEMI-AUTO "Laser/Flashlight Combo" version of BENELLI M3
location: NEW JERSEY, New Jersey, United States
postcontent:
"Why would you want to turn a semi-auto shotgun into a pump? The answer lies mostly in ammunition. Most of the self loading shotguns in my gunsmithing shop (same in my shop)are there because they aren’t functioning properly with the ammo that the user wants to shoot (usually cheap birdshot). Some “tactical” loads like reduced recoil buckshot or the so-called “beanbag” less lethal loads will fail to cycle most semi-autos regardless of how clean or lubricated they are. Add in the possibility of a fouled or muddy gun in tough real world conditions, and the idea of being able to manually pump a tactical shotgun by flipping a switch starts to make a lot more sense."
